<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Tedsig42</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/</link><description>Recent content on Tedsig42</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 19 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0100</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://tednoob17.github.io/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Google VRP: Bypassing the Fix for CVE-2022-25647</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/google-vrp-bypass-fix-of-cve-2022-25647/</link><pubDate>Sun, 19 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/google-vrp-bypass-fix-of-cve-2022-25647/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="gson-not-json"&gt;Gson, not JSON&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Gson&lt;/code&gt; (Google JSON) is an &lt;strong&gt;open-source&lt;/strong&gt; Java library developed by &lt;strong&gt;Google&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;br&gt;
Its primary purpose is to convert Java objects into their &lt;code&gt;JSON&lt;/code&gt; representation (&lt;strong&gt;serialization&lt;/strong&gt;) and to convert a &lt;code&gt;JSON&lt;/code&gt; string back into an equivalent &lt;strong&gt;Java object&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;strong&gt;deserialization&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="how-gson-works"&gt;How Gson Works&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To understand &lt;code&gt;Gson&lt;/code&gt;, think of it as a two-way bridge between your Java code and the &lt;code&gt;JSON&lt;/code&gt; format.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Serialization&lt;/strong&gt; (&lt;code&gt;Object&lt;/code&gt; -&amp;gt; &lt;code&gt;JSON&lt;/code&gt;)
If you have a &lt;strong&gt;Java object&lt;/strong&gt; (e.g., a &lt;code&gt;User&lt;/code&gt; class with a name and age), Gson &lt;strong&gt;reads&lt;/strong&gt; that object&amp;rsquo;s fields and writes them into a JSON string.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;Java: User user = new User(&amp;quot;Ted&amp;quot;, 26);&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Google VRP: To Be a Comment, or Not to Be ?</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/google-vrp-feature-not-bug/</link><pubDate>Thu, 12 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/google-vrp-feature-not-bug/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="the-hook-the-what"&gt;The Hook (The &amp;ldquo;What&amp;rdquo;)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Can a single invisible character bypass a security sandbox ? &lt;br&gt;
&lt;img src="https://tednoob17.github.io/images/stc/what-meme.gif" alt="alt text"&gt; &lt;br&gt;
I discovered a vulnerability in &lt;code&gt;google/zx&lt;/code&gt; where a Carriage Return (&lt;code&gt;\r&lt;/code&gt;) allows arbitrary code execution in Markdown files—right under the nose of code reviewers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-is-zx-"&gt;What is zx ?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In the world of DevOps, we often struggle with &lt;strong&gt;Bash&lt;/strong&gt; (which is powerful but messy) and &lt;strong&gt;Node.js&lt;/strong&gt; (which is clean but wordy).&lt;br&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;zx&lt;/strong&gt; is a tool created by &lt;strong&gt;Google&lt;/strong&gt; that marries the two.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Websec.fr Level 01</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level1/</link><pubDate>Sun, 14 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level1/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Websec.fr Level 1
&lt;code&gt;level01&lt;/code&gt; - &lt;strong&gt;1 point - 2564 solves&lt;/strong&gt;
&lt;img src="https://tednoob17.github.io/images/stc/websec-level1.png" alt="alt"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The source code for &lt;a href="http://websec.fr/level01/source.php"&gt;level1&lt;/a&gt; is shown here. Only the PHP code is included because the vulnerability is only in the PHP code.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-php" data-lang="php"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;php&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;session_start&lt;/span&gt; ();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ini_set&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;display_errors&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;on&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ini_set&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;error_reporting&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;E_ALL&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;anti_csrf.php&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;init_token&lt;/span&gt; ();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;LevelOne&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;doQuery&lt;/span&gt;($injection) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $pdo &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SQLite3&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;database.db&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SQLITE3_OPEN_READONLY&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $query &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;SELECT id,username FROM users WHERE id=&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; $injection &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39; LIMIT 1&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $getUsers &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; $pdo&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;query&lt;/span&gt;($query);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $users &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; $getUsers&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetchArray&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SQLITE3_ASSOC&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($users) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; $users;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;isset&lt;/span&gt; ($_POST[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;submit&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;isset&lt;/span&gt; ($_POST[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;user_id&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;])) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;check_and_refresh_token&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $lo &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;LevelOne&lt;/span&gt; ();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $userDetails &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; $lo&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;doQuery&lt;/span&gt; ($_POST[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;user_id&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;?&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE html&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;........
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;problem&lt;/strong&gt; here is this line &lt;code&gt;$query = 'SELECT id,username FROM users WHERE id=' . $injection . ' LIMIT 1';&lt;/code&gt; it&amp;rsquo;s a &lt;strong&gt;sqli&lt;/strong&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Websec.fr Level 04</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level4/</link><pubDate>Sun, 14 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level4/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://tednoob17.github.io/images/stc/websec-level4.png" alt="alt text"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the Level Four challenge, there are two sources: &lt;a href="http://websec.fr/level04/source1.php"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href="http://websec.fr/level04/source2.php"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Only the PHP code is shown here because the HTML is not important.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;source1.php&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-php" data-lang="php"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;php&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;connect.php&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$sql &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SQL&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$sql&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$sql&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;query&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;SELECT username FROM users WHERE id=&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;isset&lt;/span&gt; ($_COOKIE[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;leet_hax0r&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;])) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $sess_data &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;unserialize&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;base64&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;_decode&lt;/span&gt; ($_COOKIE[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;leet_hax0r&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;is_array&lt;/span&gt;($sess_data) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; $sess_data[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;ip&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!=&lt;/span&gt; $_SERVER[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;REMOTE_ADDR&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;die&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;CANT HACK US!!!&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Exception&lt;/span&gt; $e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; $e;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $cookie &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;base64_encode&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;serialize&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;array&lt;/span&gt; ( &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;ip&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; $_SERVER[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;REMOTE_ADDR&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]))) ;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;setcookie&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;leet_hax0r&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, $cookie, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;time&lt;/span&gt; () &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;86400&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;30&lt;/span&gt;));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;isset&lt;/span&gt; ($_REQUEST[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;id&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;is_numeric&lt;/span&gt; ($_REQUEST[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;id&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;])) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $sql&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;query&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.=&lt;/span&gt; $_REQUEST[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;id&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;];
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;Exception&lt;/span&gt; $e) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39; Invalid query&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;?&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;source2.php&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Websec.fr Level 08</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level8/</link><pubDate>Fri, 12 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level8/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The source code of &lt;a href="http://websec.fr/level08/index.php"&gt;level8&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href="http://websec.fr/level08/source.php"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-php" data-lang="php"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;php&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$uploadedFile &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sprintf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;%1$s/%2$s&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;/uploads&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sha1&lt;/span&gt;($_FILES[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;fileToUpload&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;][&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;name&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;.gif&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;file_exists&lt;/span&gt; ($uploadedFile)) { &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;unlink&lt;/span&gt; ($uploadedFile); }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($_FILES[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;fileToUpload&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;][&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;size&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;50000&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;getimagesize&lt;/span&gt; ($_FILES[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;fileToUpload&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;][&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;tmp_name&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;!==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;exif_imagetype&lt;/span&gt;($_FILES[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;fileToUpload&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;][&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;tmp_name&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;===&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;IMAGETYPE_GIF&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;move_uploaded_file&lt;/span&gt; ($_FILES[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;fileToUpload&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;][&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;tmp_name&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;], $uploadedFile);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;lt;p class=&amp;#34;lead&amp;#34;&amp;gt;Dump of &amp;lt;a href=&amp;#34;/level08&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; $uploadedFile &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#34;&amp;gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;htmlentities&lt;/span&gt;($_FILES[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;fileToUpload&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;][&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;name&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;lt;pre&amp;gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;include_once&lt;/span&gt;($uploadedFile);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;lt;/pre&amp;gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;unlink&lt;/span&gt;($uploadedFile);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;lt;p class=&amp;#34;text-danger&amp;#34;&amp;gt;The file is not a GIF&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;lt;p class=&amp;#34;text-danger&amp;#34;&amp;gt;The file is not an image&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;} &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;echo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;lt;p class=&amp;#34;text-danger&amp;#34;&amp;gt;The file is too big&amp;lt;/p&amp;gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;?&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;With this code we have 2 problems to bypass:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Websec.fr Level 02</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level2/</link><pubDate>Wed, 10 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level2/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The source code for &lt;a href="http://websec.fr/level02/index.php"&gt;level2&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href="http://websec.fr/level02/source.php"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://tednoob17.github.io/images/stc/level2-intro.png" alt="alt text"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-php" data-lang="php"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;php&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;ini_set&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;display_errors&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;on&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;class&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;LevelTwo&lt;/span&gt; {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;doQuery&lt;/span&gt;($injection) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $pdo &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SQLite3&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;leveltwo.db&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SQLITE3_OPEN_READONLY&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $searchWords &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;implode&lt;/span&gt; ([&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;union&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;order&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;select&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;from&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;group&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;by&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;], &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;|&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $injection &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;preg_replace&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;/&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; $searchWords &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;/i&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;, $injection);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $query &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;SELECT id,username FROM users WHERE id=&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; $injection &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39; LIMIT 1&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $getUsers &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; $pdo&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;query&lt;/span&gt; ($query);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $users &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; $getUsers&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fetchArray&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;SQLITE3_ASSOC&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ($users) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; $users;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;isset&lt;/span&gt; ($_POST[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;submit&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;isset&lt;/span&gt; ($_POST[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;user_id&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;])) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $lt &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;LevelTwo&lt;/span&gt; ();
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $userDetails &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; $lt&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;doQuery&lt;/span&gt; ($_POST[&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;user_id&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;]);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;?&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE html&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;....
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We can see that these two lines were problematic, all &lt;strong&gt;words&lt;/strong&gt; in this &lt;strong&gt;dictionary&lt;/strong&gt; are removed
from the payload.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Websec.fr Level 17</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level17/</link><pubDate>Wed, 10 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/posts/websec-fr-level17/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://tednoob17.github.io/images/stc/Level%20Seventeen.png" alt="alt text"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The code for &lt;a href="http://websec.fr/level17/index.php"&gt;level17&lt;/a&gt; is &lt;a href="http://websec.fr/level17/source.php"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-php" data-lang="php"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;lt;?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;php&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;flag.php&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;sleep_rand&lt;/span&gt;() { &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;/* I wish php5 had random_int() */&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $range &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;100000&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $bytes &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;) (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;log&lt;/span&gt;($range, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;/&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;8&lt;/span&gt;) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; { &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;/* Side effect: more random cpu cycles wasted ;) */&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; $rnd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;hexdec&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;bin2hex&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;openssl_random_pseudo_bytes&lt;/span&gt;($bytes)));
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; } &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; ($rnd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;gt;=&lt;/span&gt; $range);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;usleep&lt;/span&gt;($rnd);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;?&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE html&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;&amp;lt;html&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;.......
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; &amp;lt;?php
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; if (isset ($_POST[&amp;#39;flag&amp;#39;])):
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; sleep_rand(); /* This makes timing-attack impractical. */
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; ?&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; &amp;lt;br&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; &amp;lt;div class=&amp;#34;container&amp;#34;&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; &amp;lt;div class=&amp;#34;row&amp;#34;&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; &amp;lt;?php
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; if (! strcasecmp ($_POST[&amp;#39;flag&amp;#39;], $flag))
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; echo &amp;#39;&amp;lt;div class=&amp;#34;alert alert-success&amp;#34;&amp;gt;Here is your flag: &amp;lt;mark&amp;gt;&amp;#39; . $flag . &amp;#39;&amp;lt;/mark&amp;gt;.&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;#39;; 
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; else
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; echo &amp;#39;&amp;lt;div class=&amp;#34;alert alert-danger&amp;#34;&amp;gt;Invalid flag, sorry.&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;#39;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; ?&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; &amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt; &amp;lt;?php endif ?&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;........
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#960050;background-color:#1e0010"&gt;&amp;lt;/html&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After reading the code, we can ignore the first part of the PHP code because it&amp;rsquo;s impossible to break this function.&lt;br&gt;
But in the second part, the only thing that can lead to a vulnerability is &lt;code&gt;strcasecmp&lt;/code&gt;. This function checks if the input matches the &lt;strong&gt;flag&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;
Reading &lt;a href="https://www.php.net/manual/fr/function.strcasecmp.php"&gt;strcasecmp php documentation&lt;/a&gt; we can see that :&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Why Book Review ?</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/why-book-review/</link><pubDate>Wed, 10 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/why-book-review/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;In this section, I share reviews of books I use to learn and improve in infosec.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be two review formats:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Some books will be covered through multiple chapters/posts to go deeper step by step.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Others will be treated in a single post with a fast global summary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most of the books come from publishers like &lt;strong&gt;No Starch Press&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong&gt;O&amp;rsquo;Reilly&lt;/strong&gt;, or &lt;strong&gt;Packt Publishing&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I personally started infosec by reading &lt;a href="https://phrack.org"&gt;Phrack&lt;/a&gt; and solving &lt;a href="https://www.root-me.org/"&gt;Root-Me&lt;/a&gt; challenges, and I believe books are still one of the best ways to build strong fundamentals.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>x86-64 Assembly Language Programming with Ubuntu written by Ed Jorgensen</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/x86-64-assembly-language-programming-with-ubuntu/</link><pubDate>Wed, 10 Dec 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/x86-64-assembly-language-programming-with-ubuntu/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;I am starting with the book &lt;code&gt;x86-64 Assembly Language Programming with Ubuntu&lt;/code&gt; , written by &lt;a href="https://www.legacy.com/us/obituaries/name/edward-jorgensen-obituary?id=59464082"&gt;Dr. Ed Jorgensen&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;
I use &lt;code&gt;mdBook&lt;/code&gt; to take notes and make diagrams, often with &lt;a href="https://excalidraw.com/"&gt;Excalidraw&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;br&gt;
Why? Because I want to learn it, and it can be useful in the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The book is published under a &lt;strong&gt;Creative Commons&lt;/strong&gt; license, so you can get it &lt;a href="https://www.cl72.org/120introAssem/assembly-language64-ubuntu.pdf"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My work can be found &lt;a href="https://tednoob17.github.io/x86-64-assembly-language/"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>From Day 0 to 0day Chapter 2</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/from-day0-to-0day-chapter-2/</link><pubDate>Wed, 06 Aug 2025 00:22:36 +1300</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/from-day0-to-0day-chapter-2/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://tednoob17.github.io/images/stc/chap2.jpeg" alt="alt"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id="mapping-code-to-attack-surface"&gt;MAPPING CODE TO ATTACK SURFACE&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Once we know where we are, then the world becomes as narrow as a map.&lt;br&gt;
When we don’t know, the world feels unlimited.
&lt;code&gt;Liu Cixin, The Dark Forest&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="introduction"&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attack surface&lt;/strong&gt; (the potential entry points to exploit a vulnerability) often increases with the growing
&lt;strong&gt;complexity&lt;/strong&gt; of software.&lt;br&gt;
The &lt;strong&gt;vulnerabilities&lt;/strong&gt; to be introduced, as developers’ capacity to &lt;strong&gt;properly secure&lt;/strong&gt; these feature is
limited and mistakes are &lt;strong&gt;inevitable&lt;/strong&gt; when dealing with millions of lines of code.&lt;br&gt;
Minor issues can be &lt;strong&gt;chained&lt;/strong&gt; together into far more serious &lt;strong&gt;vulnerabilities&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>From Day 0 to 0day Chapter 1</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/from-day0-to-0day-chapter-1/</link><pubDate>Sun, 03 Aug 2025 00:10:42 +0200</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/from-day0-to-0day-chapter-1/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://tednoob17.github.io/images/stc/chap2-intro.jpeg" alt="alt"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="introduction"&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2 id="taint-analysis"&gt;Taint Analysis&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Life is not like water. Things in life don’t necessarily flow over the shortest possible route&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;code&gt;Haruki Murakami - 1Q84&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Taint analysis&lt;/strong&gt; (or &lt;strong&gt;source and sink analysis&lt;/strong&gt; ) is the analysis of the flow of &lt;strong&gt;input&lt;/strong&gt; through a &lt;strong&gt;program&lt;/strong&gt; from &lt;strong&gt;sources to sinks&lt;/strong&gt; .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It relies on a simple idea: a large number of vulnerabilities occur because attacker &lt;strong&gt;controlled input&lt;/strong&gt; (the &lt;strong&gt;source&lt;/strong&gt;) flows to a dangerous &lt;strong&gt;function&lt;/strong&gt; (the &lt;strong&gt;sink&lt;/strong&gt;).
If the input modifies other variables along the way, these
variables become &amp;ldquo;&lt;strong&gt;tainted&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;rdquo; and are included in the analysis.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>From Day 0 to 0day Chapter 0</title><link>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/from-day0-to-0day-chapter-0/</link><pubDate>Tue, 15 Jul 2025 00:37:02 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://tednoob17.github.io/book-reviews/from-day0-to-0day-chapter-0/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src="https://tednoob17.github.io/images/stc/fd0t0d.png" alt="alt"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is my summary and review of the book &lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://nostarch.com/zero-day"&gt;From Day Zero to Zero Day&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; by Eugene &amp;ldquo;&lt;a href="https://x.com/spaceraccoonsec"&gt;Spaceraccoon&lt;/a&gt;&amp;rdquo; Lim, a security researcher and white-hat hacker.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;He learned rapidly because his first training was in how to learn.&lt;/strong&gt; - &lt;code&gt;Frank Herbert, Dune&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the number of discovered and exploited zero days constantly growing, vulnerability research, or the process of analyzing systems
for new vulnerabilities, has assumed a critical role in cybersecurity.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>